[Episode 36]

9
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:06,030
[Xiaoyu's Private Kitchen]

10
00:01:14,020 --> 00:01:14,870
Brother Fatty.

11
00:01:14,870 --> 00:01:17,010
Kesong, you are here.

12
00:01:17,010 --> 00:01:18,520
Aunty Xu is in the back.

13
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:20,380
- Okay
- Go ahead.

14
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:26,340
Kesong?

15
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:28,460
Hurry. Hurry. Hurry. Hurry. Hurry and sit. Come sit.

16
00:01:28,460 --> 00:01:29,530
Sit.

17
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:31,290
- Sit.
- Okay.

18
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:35,140
- Kesong.
- What's going on?

19
00:01:35,140 --> 00:01:39,020
Xiao Jiang really can't see?

20
00:01:40,870 --> 00:01:42,770
Yes.

21
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:45,660
But maybe he'll be able to see tomorrow.

22
00:01:45,660 --> 00:01:47,430
Is his mood especially low?

23
00:01:47,430 --> 00:01:50,440
Do you even need to ask?

24
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:55,400
That... That... Xiao Jiang lost his sense of taste,

25
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:59,050
your dad and I already saw on TV.

26
00:01:59,050 --> 00:02:02,240
Thinking that with you by his side, it isn't a big problem.

27
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,910
So we didn't say anything.

28
00:02:04,910 --> 00:02:07,110
Right?

29
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:09,570
Your mom and I are usually very strict with you.

30
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:12,420
But now you're grown up. You have your own thoughts.

31
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:14,580
We shouldn't meddle.

32
00:02:14,580 --> 00:02:19,120
But this time it's different. These are eyes. Eyes are the window to the soul.

33
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:23,380
That's a stretch. What do eyes have to do with windows?

34
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:29,060
Kesong, such a big thing happened. Why didn't you tell us?

35
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:34,090
This is not an extremely big thing, so I didn't say anything.

36
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:39,650
You... My daughter, you're putting on too big of an act.

37
00:02:39,650 --> 00:02:42,520
But it hasn't affected me much.

38
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,600
You really guessed it.

39
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:47,930
This... Mom will just speak honestly.

40
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:52,760
That... That... Have you fallen for Xiao Jiang?

41
00:03:03,010 --> 00:03:06,310
Actually, after you left last time,

42
00:03:07,570 --> 00:03:10,030
a lot of things happened.

43
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,180
He's the type of person...

44
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:19,460
I won't talk about his cooking.

45
00:03:21,460 --> 00:03:23,720
He's the type of person

46
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:26,190
who only looks fierce.

47
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:28,800
He is very simple-hearted.

48
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:31,330
He is also good to those around him.

49
00:03:31,330 --> 00:03:33,600
No matter what happens,

50
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,050
he always wants to be in front of me.

51
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:42,040
After being with him, I feel like

52
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:45,160
the days get better and better.

53
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:49,400
I want to know, is he good to you?

54
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:54,840
He treats me well. In fact, better and better.

55
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:01,550
Last time when your dad and I came to Shanghai, we asked about you and Xiao Jiang.

56
00:04:01,550 --> 00:04:03,330
We didn't mean anything by it.

57
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:05,980
We were just afraid that you'd get hurt and lied to.

58
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,660
After I returned with your dad, we said

59
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:12,390
that we won't ask about your business as much.

60
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:14,940
After all, you've grown up.

61
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:16,990
You should have your own love life.

62
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,610
Right.

63
00:04:18,610 --> 00:04:23,760
But if Xiao Jiang were able to see,

64
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,200
we wouldn't say anything.

65
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:29,850
But you chose to be with someone who can't see.

66
00:04:29,850 --> 00:04:33,170
Do you know how hard that path will be?

67
00:04:33,170 --> 00:04:34,740
Do you know?

68
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:37,100
How would I know?

69
00:04:37,690 --> 00:04:40,190
But I'm not afraid.

70
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:44,420
I'm very happy being with him now.

71
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:48,990
If there are problems, we'll overcome them together.

72
00:04:48,990 --> 00:04:51,170
So, do you agree to us being together?

73
00:04:51,170 --> 00:04:56,180
I… Your dad and I are both troubled and confused.

74
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:59,110
We're concerned about whether you will live well.

75
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,850
No, Kesong,

76
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:05,490
your mom and I lived life without trial or tribulation.

77
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:09,200
The more peaceful, the better. We think that this is happiness.

78
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:12,660
So we want you to walk the same path as us.

79
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:15,460
- Right. Right. Right. Right.
- But now you've chosen a very tough path.

80
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:18,530
This path is very hard. You must think it through.

81
00:05:18,530 --> 00:05:22,240
We.. we're not saying this to stop you. We're saying

82
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:25,430
if you've thought it through, then Dad supports you.

83
00:05:27,130 --> 00:05:28,820
Right?

84
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:37,330
Right? We won't meddle so much. We'll let our daughter handle it.

85
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:41,220
As a child, you'll think that mom and dad nag too much.

86
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:43,190
And that they're so fussy.

87
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:46,600
But now after running into problems,

88
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,640
I know how fortunate I am.

89
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:52,880
They understand you and support you,

90
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:56,290
and make sure you don't have any worries.

91
00:05:56,290 --> 00:06:00,080
This must be what the world's best parents are like.

92
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:05,070
Mom and Dad, to be your daughter,

93
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:07,930
is my life's biggest pride.

94
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:30,060
I think she fell in love with Jiang Qianfan.

95
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:32,730
Disappointed?

96
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:34,470
Not really.

97
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:36,830
I just feel that Old Lin is drifting away from me.

98
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:39,640
I used to think that I was a star

99
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:42,200
and that she was the satellite next to me.

100
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,730
She ran circles around me.

101
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:47,510
It's like she never strayed off that track.

102
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:50,740
She became a habit in my life.

103
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:55,160
But it's not like that anymore. She's a small universe herself now.

104
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:57,980
She is gaining a lot more capabilities.

105
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:01,270
And I've become dumber and can't do anything right.

106
00:07:10,010 --> 00:07:11,870
Yours.

107
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:24,860
This is your first job. Not doing it right is normal.

108
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:29,180
I'm telling you, at my first job, I was more of a noob than you.

109
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:31,250
Ah? That can't be.

110
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,390
A rich heiress like you has had a job before?

111
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,100
Yes.

112
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:38,260
After the college entrance examination,

113
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:41,000
I worked in a restaurant similar to this one.

114
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,680
At first, I thought that being a waitress would be very simple.

115
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,060
It's just taking orders and carrying trays.

116
00:07:46,060 --> 00:07:49,810
But one time, I took an entire table's order

117
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:51,280
and lost it.

118
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:53,490
I thought, since I made a mistake, then I'll go apologize.

119
00:07:53,490 --> 00:07:54,840
I'll take their order again.

120
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:59,080
But not only did they not accept my apology, they even overturned the table.

121
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:01,520
The table hit me.

122
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:05,400
Then what did you do? Did you leave right away, or call your dad over to beat them up?

123
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,200
How could I do that?

124
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,470
My dad said while trying to make a name for myself,

125
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:12,750
it's only right for me to face the consequences for my mistakes.

126
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:14,900
If you should compensate, then compensate. If you should apologize, then apologize.

127
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:20,060
But after work, I went somewhere with nobody around. Cried my eyes out.

128
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:21,880
Wasn't I silly?

129
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,550
Yes.

130
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:26,100
I didn't expect you to have such a history.

131
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,720
Alright,

132
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:31,830
I should be content with a boss like you.

133
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:34,560
I won't complain anymore. I'll do my best.

134
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:37,160
You got this.

135
00:08:37,730 --> 00:08:39,320
¥35.

136
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,680
Which one is good?

137
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:42,510
This one tastes better.

138
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:44,540
Okay.

139
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:45,860
Boss.

140
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:48,510
- How much for one of these?
- That's ¥5 each.

141
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:51,530
- Give me around seven to eight.
- Alright.

142
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,010
Sure.

143
00:08:55,010 --> 00:08:56,980
What is that?

144
00:09:01,130 --> 00:09:03,570
Do you like it?

145
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:05,630
You have four leaf clovers here?

146
00:09:05,630 --> 00:09:09,600
That's not for sale. It's our lucky clover.

147
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:16,000
Congratulations. You'll have good luck after seeing it.

148
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,290
I'm home.

149
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:49,720
You're back.

150
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:52,840
No need to shake. I can't see.

151
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,250
How did you hold it?

152
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:04,290
I originally thought I couldn't do it.

153
00:11:04,290 --> 00:11:07,670
I was going to try it while you were away.

154
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:11,070
But, unexpectedly, I can do it pretty easily.

155
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:14,360
Later, I realized it's probably I've done it a lot

156
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:17,130
that they've become an instinct.

157
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:25,330
Four-leaf clover, thank you.

158
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:27,940
What clover?

159
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:32,090
It's nothing.

160
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:36,820
Do you remember? When we were in Hangzhou,

161
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,750
you even bought me Ice Milk Shake.

162
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:42,350
I thought it wasn't good, and said the temperature wasn't 80 degrees.

163
00:11:42,350 --> 00:11:44,640
I'm making a correct one for you.

164
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,190
You still remember that time?

165
00:11:47,190 --> 00:11:50,890
If it's anything to do with you, I don't forget.

166
00:11:54,460 --> 00:11:56,250
It should be ready now.

167
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:04,870
Here.

168
00:12:10,050 --> 00:12:11,760
Drink it. How is it?

169
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,880
Why is it sweet?

170
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,330
I added sugar.

171
00:12:18,330 --> 00:12:21,470
I mean, why did you add sugar?

172
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:24,150
Actually, I thought it over a lot later on.

173
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:26,760
Even though my eyes are blind now,

174
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:30,440
but I can actually see more clearly now, by seeing my heart.

175
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:34,250
Previously, I resisted sugar. Wherever I was,

176
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:38,260
I forbade sugar. But later I realized,

177
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:43,120
I never evaded it. The sugar was always next to me.

178
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:47,300
Where? I tried looking for it a few times but never saw it.

179
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:49,640
Aren't you silly?

180
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:54,880
You are my sugar.

181
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:59,510
Even though we haven't been together for long,

182
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:02,380
and we are arguing and fussing most of the time,

183
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:04,680
but at this time,

184
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:07,840
when I recall it, it's especially sweet.

185
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,840
Every moment is sweet.

186
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:15,820
So I can't think of another reason to resist the sugar.

187
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:20,690
Just like myself, I can't think of a reason to refuse you.

188
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,410
Thank you.

189
00:13:35,010 --> 00:13:37,410
I will never forget

190
00:13:38,470 --> 00:13:41,330
your gaze, when I first

191
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:44,000
laid eyes on you.

192
00:13:45,990 --> 00:13:48,530
Do you believe it?

193
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:52,060
I have never seen anyone's eyes like yours.

194
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:55,090
So clean.

195
00:13:55,090 --> 00:13:59,820
So beautiful. When I saw you the first time,

196
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,630
I knew I liked you.

197
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:08,360
I'll never forget

198
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:12,620
your confident expression in the hotel.

199
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:15,690
You looked fearless.

200
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,560
From that moment on, I knew

201
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:22,730
if I didn't leave right away,

202
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:25,920
I wouldn't let you go.

203
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:28,820
So that's what you thought at that time.

204
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:33,350
Same for me.

205
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:38,620
I've never met anyone like you who is so double-faced.

206
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:41,320
You looked so fierce,

207
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:45,160
but your heart is so soft.

208
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,460
Silly.

209
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:50,850
Humans are complicated.

210
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:55,130
Later, when I learned that

211
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,770
you were the person who I was looking for,

212
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:03,800
I was really shocked.

213
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:08,290
From the first moment that I saw you,

214
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:12,990
I kept reminding myself

215
00:15:12,990 --> 00:15:15,190
not to fall for you.

216
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:17,850
Absolutely not.

217
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:23,330
But I couldn't do it.

218
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,890
Do you remember the day we argued?

219
00:15:32,630 --> 00:15:34,730
I kicked you out?

220
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:39,580
That night, I had a nightmare.

221
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:41,620
In my dream,

222
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:45,060
you were everywhere.

223
00:15:47,220 --> 00:15:50,600
That's the first time that I felt in my life

224
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:55,190
that my heart was being held in someone's hand.

225
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:57,750
It hurt.

226
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:59,620
It felt real.

227
00:15:59,620 --> 00:16:01,720
Such a coincidence.

228
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,840
I dreamed of you that day, too.

229
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:11,340
I dreamed that you came in and hugged me like this.

230
00:16:11,340 --> 00:16:13,720
You didn't say a word.

231
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:18,400
When I woke up, I saw that I was by myself.

232
00:16:21,170 --> 00:16:23,550
I felt sad.

233
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:28,680
Sorry.

234
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,560
It's my fault.

235
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,060
Can you believe

236
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:41,080
I had a dream that's just like now.

237
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:45,400
In the dream, I hugged you like I'm hugging you now.

238
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:48,130
Exactly the same.

239
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:51,990
Turns out caring about each other

240
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,030
is so good.

241
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:59,460
But, I'm sorry.

242
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:03,700
I know that

243
00:17:05,220 --> 00:17:08,060
I can't not give you the best version of me.

244
00:17:14,330 --> 00:17:16,720
Aren't you silly?

245
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,100
How do you know which version of you

246
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,300
is the best?

247
00:17:25,840 --> 00:17:28,760
Do you know what I like the most about you?

248
00:17:30,230 --> 00:17:32,160
What?

249
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:36,970
Your persistence.

250
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:41,230
The persistence to culinary arts.

251
00:17:41,230 --> 00:17:43,190
The persistence to feelings.

252
00:17:45,970 --> 00:17:48,430
But I don't understand any of it.

253
00:17:51,060 --> 00:17:53,820
I don't understand this ridiculous world.

254
00:17:56,660 --> 00:17:59,170
I don't understand those laughable people.

255
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:04,660
The only thing I know

256
00:18:06,150 --> 00:18:08,430
is cooking.

257
00:18:08,430 --> 00:18:10,830
What I probably like

258
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:15,190
is this simple and pure you.

259
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:23,370
♫  To embrace the rising storm  ♫

260
00:18:23,370 --> 00:18:26,000
You don't need to understand this world.

261
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:30,300
You only need to remember this,

262
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:32,990
you love me,

263
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,390
and I love you. That's enough.

264
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,830
Okay.

265
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,420
I promise you.

266
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:10,390
I want you to feed me.

267
00:19:12,830 --> 00:19:14,520
Okay.

268
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:30,470
If I even need me to feed you when you eat,

269
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:33,960
does this mean I'm in charge of this household?

270
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:36,230
You want to be in charge?

271
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:38,100
Sure.

272
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:41,920
What are you so boring? You must say, no way.

273
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:44,400
Okay. No way.

274
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,450
No way, but it's still the case nonetheless.

275
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:52,630
Remember you set up a lot of rules for me when I first came?

276
00:19:52,630 --> 00:19:54,700
It's my turn now.

277
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,230
Are you revenging against me?

278
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:00,250
You just realized?

279
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:06,000
However, I'm much kinder than you. You set up so many rules for me, but I only have one for you.

280
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,170
Tell me about it.

281
00:20:07,170 --> 00:20:10,490
You just listen to me on everything.

282
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,530
Everything?

283
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,170
What's everything?

284
00:20:20,170 --> 00:20:22,330
You are everything.

285
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:24,390
I like this answer.

286
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:27,670
You've misled me.

287
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:42,770
- Let's see who it is.
- You want to ambush me?

288
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:45,430
It's Thomas.

289
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:50,000
Hello, Mr. Thomas.

290
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,890
What did he say?

291
00:20:52,890 --> 00:20:56,890
Mr. Thomas said that the committee has drafted two announcements.

292
00:20:56,890 --> 00:21:00,020
The first statement says “Jiang Qianfan

293
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:03,190
has decided to withdraw from the finals due to his blindness."

294
00:21:03,190 --> 00:21:06,310
The second is, "despite losing his sight, Jiang Qianfan

295
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:10,480
has decided to join the finals." He is asking you which one you'd choose.

296
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:14,860
Tell him not to ask if he already knows the answer.

297
00:21:14,860 --> 00:21:19,600
Is he looking for an excuse to ask about my well-being?

298
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:22,960
Mr. Thomas, Mr. Jiang...

299
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:33,010
Okay. Don't worry.

300
00:21:39,620 --> 00:21:41,860
Why are you so smart?

301
00:21:41,860 --> 00:21:45,630
You are right. He told me to take good care of you.

302
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:53,620
I was going to kiss you.

303
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:56,630
Why did you aim so right?

304
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:03,170
I think I can see some light.

305
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,550
This is really a miracle.

306
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:21,530
I thought your blindness is irreversible.

307
00:22:21,530 --> 00:22:23,930
I didn't expect you to restore your sense of light.

308
00:22:23,930 --> 00:22:25,900
If this continues, it won't take long

309
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,740
before you restore your sight.

310
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,860
If it really works out, it's wonderful.

311
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:34,680
Can you tell me what you've experienced?

312
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:39,530
Kesong, can you tell him?

313
00:22:51,250 --> 00:22:58,270
